        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 2:25PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 224 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a slow-moving thunderstorm
near Long Grove, or 12 miles north of Bettendorf. This storm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Minor flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Slowing or redirecting of traffic due to ponding or flowing
water. Closure of waterfront access due to flooding.

Locations impacted include...
Long Grove, McCausland, Scott County Park, and Park View.

Rainfall amounts up to 1 inch have fallen and an additional 1 to 2
inches of rain are possible.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring and may lead to localized flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways. Stay away from
flooded areas. Report any flooding to local law enforcement.</instruction>
